      "id": "PopularPost361521",
      "post_content": "@RedJaron  \n  \nActually, if they have one card in hand and you trigger this ability in response to them casting said card, it's still cast and you've wasted a heroic trigger; Just like a counterspell, responding to someone casting something occurs after the card has left their hand but before it's resolved. AS it's being cast you put something on the stack ahead of it.",
